    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-02-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-02-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="60"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d60">
                <head>60. Memorandum From the <gloss type="from">Joint Chiefs of Staff</gloss> to
                    the Secretary of Defense (<persName corresp="#p_WCE1" type="to"
                        >Wilson</persName>)<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d60fn1">Source:
                        Department of State, <gloss target="#t_SS1">S/S</gloss>–<gloss
                            target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files: Lot 63 D 351, <gloss
                            target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 5602 Series. Top Secret.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <hi rend="italic">
                            <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                                when="1956-02-24">February 24, 1956</date>.</hi>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Review of Basic National Security Policy, <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                            >NSC</gloss> 5602</item>
                </list>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>The Joint Chiefs of Staff forward in the Enclosure<note n="2"
                            xml:id="d60fn2">Not printed.</note> hereto their comments on <gloss
                            target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 5602. They consider that these comments, if
                        adopted, will clarify certain important aspects of this paper.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>The Joint Chiefs of Staff are, however, more concerned with the over-all
                        aspects of <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 5602 which in their opinion
                        is in essence a restatement of the Basic National Security Policy as
                        contained in both <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 5501 and <gloss
                            target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 162/2.<note n="3" xml:id="d60fn3">For text
                            of <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 162/2, “Basic National Security
                            Policy,” dated October 30, 1953, see <ref
                                target="frus1952-54v02p1#pg_577">
                                <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, vol. II, Part 1, p.
                                577</ref>.</note> They feel strongly that there has been a marked
                        deterioration of the Free World position in the past year, due mainly to a
                        new and more flexible approach on the part of the Communist Bloc (<gloss
                            target="#t_USSR1">USSR</gloss>). Unless U.S. policy is realistically
                        revised to meet the new Soviet tactics, U.S. leadership of the Free World
                        will be jeopardized.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Accordingly, the Joint Chiefs of Staff recommend that, regardless of
                        action taken by the National Security Council on <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                            >NSC</gloss> 5602, a complete restudy of the Basic National Security
                        Policy be made as a matter of urgency.</item>
                </list>
                <p rend="right">For the Joint Chiefs of Staff:</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RAAM1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Arthur Radford</hi>
                        </persName>
                        <note n="4" xml:id="d60fn4">Printed from a copy that bears this typed
                            signature.</note>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chairman<lb/>Joint Chiefs of Staff</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
